<title>UK: Gerrard &amp; National suffers profits slump.</title>
<headline>Gerrard &amp; National suffers profits slump.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>half year to September 30</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		8.4		    vs 15.6</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 8.0		    vs 8.0</p>
<p> Pretax operating	 6.3		    vs 12.1</p>
<p> Operating income	 43.4		   vs 51.2</p>
<p> Tax			  2.0		    vs 4.2</p>
<p> Profit after tax	 4.3		    vs 7.8</p>
<p> Attributable	     4.1		    vs 7.6</p>
<p> Pay date		   December 13 1996</p>
<p>Div registration date  November 5 1996</p>
<p>NOTE -- Financial services provider and stockbroker Gerrard &amp; National Plc said in its results statement: &quot;The introduction of the gilt repo market, reduced turnover in foreign exchange and increasing margin pressure in derivative markets combined to create a particularly challenging environment.&quot;</p>
</text>
